    "text": "1.1 Finding triangles\nimport math\ndef find_xyz(n = 40):\n    m = math.ceil(n / 3)\n    c = 0\n    re = list()\n    for x in range(1, m + 1):\n        for y in range(x, n + 1):\n            z = n - (x + y)\n            if z &gt;= y and x + y &gt; z:\n                c += 1\n                re.append((x, y, z))\n    return [c, re]\n\ncount, results = find_xyz(40)\n\nprint(f\"Number of solutions: {count}\")\nprint(\"Solutions:\")\nfor triple in results:\n    print(triple)\n\nNumber of solutions: 33\nSolutions:\n(2, 19, 19)\n(3, 18, 19)\n(4, 17, 19)\n(4, 18, 18)\n(5, 16, 19)\n(5, 17, 18)\n(6, 15, 19)\n(6, 16, 18)\n(6, 17, 17)\n(7, 14, 19)\n(7, 15, 18)\n(7, 16, 17)\n(8, 13, 19)\n(8, 14, 18)\n(8, 15, 17)\n(8, 16, 16)\n(9, 12, 19)\n(9, 13, 18)\n(9, 14, 17)\n(9, 15, 16)\n(10, 11, 19)\n(10, 12, 18)\n(10, 13, 17)\n(10, 14, 16)\n(10, 15, 15)\n(11, 11, 18)\n(11, 12, 17)\n(11, 13, 16)\n(11, 14, 15)\n(12, 12, 16)\n(12, 13, 15)\n(12, 14, 14)\n(13, 13, 14)",
